We are launching a new STEM science kit called "Discovery Lab: Volcanoes" for 5th‑grade classrooms. Here is the teacher persona we want to target:

```json
{
  "persona_name": "teacher_5th_grade",
  "demographics": {
    "age_range": "30-45",
    "experience": "3-10 years teaching science",
    "location": "US"
  },
  "psychographics": {
    "values": ["hands‑on learning", "curriculum alignment", "student engagement"],
    "pain_points": ["limited lab time", "budget constraints", "need for easy setup"]
  }
}
```

Our brand voice should be encouraging, upbeat, and use simple, vivid language. Here are the brand guidelines:

```json
{
  "tone": "encouraging",
  "vocabulary": ["exciting", "discover", "ignite curiosity"],
  "style": {
    "sentence_length": "short to medium",
    "avoid_jargon": true,
    "use_active_voice": true
  }
}
```
